Banco Popolare SC may sell units
Credito Bergamasco and Cassa di Risparmio di Lucca, Pisa e
Livorno for around 3 billion euros, MF reported, without saying
where it got the information.  The bank is also considering a 2 billion-euro capital
increase as an alternative to asset sales, MF said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
